reference "fig:Existing-PHY-Layer-anti-collisio"

\end_inset

 shows the most common physical layer anti-collision protocols, which are:
 FDMA, SDMA, CDMA and TDMA.
 These algorithms will be briefly discussed in the following paragraphs:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Frequency Division Multiple Access (FDMA):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this protocol, the frequency band is divided into different sub-frequency
 bands and tags are distributed among them 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "FDMA"

\end_inset

.
 However, this technique adds complexity to the system.
 Readers should be able to decode different frequencies at the same time.
 Moreover, tags should be able to select its desirable sub-channel, which
 is incompatible with EPCglobal C1 G2.
 Only active tags can do such functionality.
