\end_inset

, tag 4 transmits in the first slot alone.
 Thus, it is a successful slot.
 In the second slot, no tag has replied.
 So, it is an empty slot.
 In the third slot, tags 3 and 4 have replied together, which results in
 a collided slot.
 According to the FSA rules, tags 3 and 4 are not allowed to resubmit their
 IDs again during the same frame.
 Thus in slot 
\begin_inset Formula $4$
\end_inset

, tag 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 only is allowed to reply to have another successful slot.
 In the next frame, the same procedure is repeated until all tags are identified.
 
